      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACK MARVEL (2) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 2.75 lengths at Shepparton in a handy 22.30 beating Ram Raid. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to his name from six starts. Can continue the winning form. PAW WALDO (1) has been out of the placings at his last couple but on the winners' heels when placing three back (19.49) in a Grade 5 at this track. Can turn it around this time. ELECTRA OPAL (8) made light work of the tricky draw with a scorching early sectional but swamped late when a close up fourth (16.82) at this track over 300m. The form out of her last race has been franked. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. STAR REBEL (3) drops in distance and is worth considering.",
